I’ve replaced the Scala `for ((record, batchIndex) <- batch.asScala.view.zipWithIndex)` comprehensions in both non‐compressed paths with explicit `while` loops and `Iterator`s to eliminate the per‐record tuple and view allocations, reducing garbage and improving iteration performance.

